# Phase 38: Fraud Detection & Defensive Architecture

This phase transforms VibeStream from a "secure" platform to an "actively defensive" one. By implementing real-time behavioral scoring and silent mitigation (shadow banning), we protect the platform's economic and engagement integrity.

## Proposed Changes

### 🛡️ Core Fraud Engine [SQL]
#### [NEW] [phase-38-fraud-engine.sql](file:///C:/GOLive/scripts/phase-38-fraud-engine.sql)
- **Signal Layer**: `fraud_events` table and `user_fraud_features` materialized view.
- **Brain Layer**: `get_user_risk_score` function for real-time behavioral analysis.
- **Defense Layer**: `is_shadow_banned` flag on profiles and `apply_shadow_ban` utility.
- **Hardening**: `check_rate_limit` helper and atomic `toggle_like` refactor.

### 🎥 Engagement API [Next.js]
#### [MODIFY] [track-view/route.ts](file:///C:/GOLive/app/api/video/track-view/route.ts)
- Integrate `blocked` status check from `track_video_view`.
- Enhance server-side IP extraction logic.

#### [MODIFY] [WatchClient.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/app/watch/[id]/WatchClient.tsx)
- Ensure all engagement calls (likes, hypes) are compatible with the hardened RPC signatures.

### 💰 Tipping System [SQL/API]
#### [NEW] `create_tip` RPC
- Replace direct `tip_transactions` INSERTs with a fraud-aware RPC.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- **Bot Simulation**: Script to attempt 100+ views from same IP/Session to verify rate limiting and risk score spike.
- **Shadow Ban Verification**: Manually shadow-ban a test account and verify that its likes/views no longer increment public counters.

### Manual Verification
- Verify that the "Vibe Intelligence" dashboard still shows accurate data despite the defensive layering.
